---
// Hero + problem strip (GP-159). All copy verbatim from
// docs/website-presentation.md (§1, §2, §12). The visual is a real GP-37
// export of PR #42 in asteriusit/groundplan-example — rendered by the
// server exporter, not drawn for the website (see assets-src/render-hero.ts).
---

<div class="blueprint-grid border-b border-border">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pt-16 pb-12 sm:px-6 sm:pt-24">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">
      Terraform &amp; Kubernetes · living architecture diagrams
    </p>
    <h1
      class="mt-5 max-w-3xl font-display text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-6xl"
    >
      <span class="text-primary">See</span> your infrastructure.
      <span class="text-primary">Review</span> it.
      <span class="text-primary">Shape</span> it.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
      Groundplan turns Terraform and Kubernetes into living, interactive architecture
      diagrams — so teams review infrastructure changes visually, keep documentation
      permanently in sync with code, and see their cloud the way they think about it:
      as networks, permissions and systems, not thousands of lines of HCL.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
      <a
        href="/security/"
        class="bg-primary px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground hover:opacity-90"
      >
        We ingest data, not access — see how
      </a>
      <a href="#pillars" class="px-2 py-2.5 text-sm text-secondary-foreground hover:text-foreground">
        Explore the three pillars ↓
      </a>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs text-muted-foreground">
      One pipeline step away from seeing your infrastructure.
    </p>

    <figure class="mt-12">
      <div class="border border-border-strong bg-card shadow-sm">
        <img
          src="/images/hero-pr-diagram.svg"
          alt="A Groundplan pull-request diagram of PR #42 in asteriusit/groundplan-example: a created Redis cache, private endpoint and Key Vault secret in green, an updated web app in amber, a deleted storage account in dashed red, and an impacted diagnostic setting in violet, with the unchanged estate ghosted."
          width="1912"
          height="751"
          class="block h-auto w-full"
          fetchpriority="high"
        />
      </div>
      <figcaption class="mt-2 font-mono text-[11px] text-faint">
        PR #42 · asteriusit/groundplan-example · exported by the Groundplan renderer
        (same pipeline as PR comments and share links)
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <aside class="mt-10 max-w-3xl border-l-2 border-primary bg-card p-5">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">
        Trust model
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>We ingest data, not access.</strong> Groundplan reads the plan JSON and
        rendered manifests your own CI produces. It never holds cloud credentials, never
        reads your Terraform state, never runs <code class="font-mono text-sm">terraform</code>,
        <code class="font-mono text-sm">helm</code> or
        <code class="font-mono text-sm">kustomize</code>. Adoption is one pipeline step.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</div>

<section aria-label="The problem" class="border-b border-border bg-card">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6">
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 divide-y divide-border sm:grid-cols-2 sm:divide-y-0 lg:grid-cols-4 lg:divide-x">
      <li class="py-6 sm:px-5 sm:py-8 lg:first:pl-0">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-delete">review</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          Infra review is text review — reviewers approve plans nobody can picture.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="py-6 sm:px-5 sm:py-8">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-delete">documentation</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          Architecture documentation is dead the day it's drawn.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="py-6 sm:px-5 sm:py-8">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-delete">blast radius</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          The blast radius of a change is invisible until it detonates.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="py-6 sm:px-5 sm:py-8 lg:last:pr-0">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-delete">access</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          Existing visualisers demand read access to your cloud or your state.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
